setFragmentTextures( _ [ MTLTexture? ], range: Range<Int> ex. N ..< N + M )
NOTE: Multiple textures of variable numbers M with the starting index N can be specified with the following pair of APIs.
- array< texture2d<float>, M> texes [[ ... ]] in the formal parameters of the fragment shader.
M must be determined at the compilation time. However, at runtime, not all the M elements must be specified in [MTLTexture?].
In the fragment shader each texture can be accessed by array indexing, i.e., texes[N+i].
